# Documentation on change (required)

When you **change app behavior**, **add a feature**, **add/alter a migration**, or **change user-visible UX**, update documentation in the **same task** (same PR/commit). Do not ship code-only unless the user explicitly asks to skip docs.

## Minimum checklist

1. **Identify impact** — UI, RPC/DB, settings, tests, deploy.
2. **Update mapped docs** (below) — remove stale text (e.g. removed UI, old flows).
3. **Migrations** — add step to `app/supabase/README.txt`; note in `docs/backend/phase1-use-cases-and-tests.md` pre-flight if tests need it.
4. **Changelog** — one bullet in `docs/LLM_CONTEXT.md` (newest first, date + what changed).
5. **Tests** — extend or update `app/scripts/e2e-*.mjs` in the **same PR** when behavior is testable (source grep, routes, live RPC/DB). Do not change Tier A/B/C/UI/patterns code without touching the matching e2e script (see table below).
6. **Manual QA** — add/adjust rows in `docs/backend/phase1-manual-e2e-checklist.md` (§2 catalog + §3 steps + §1 Gaps if needed). Phase 0 sign-off: `docs/PHASE0_SIGNOFF.md` only (do not revive `docs/archive/YOUR_TURN_*.md`).

